      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $n,p \\in \\N$. On note $\\Gamma_n^p$ le nombre de $n$-uplets\n$(x_1,\\dots, x_n) \\in \\N^n$ tels que $x_1 + \\dots + x_n = p$.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n,p \\in \\N\\)</span>. On note <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^p\\)</span> le nombre de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span>-uplets <span class=\"math inline\">\\((x_1,\\dots, x_n) \\in \\N^n\\)</span> tels que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x_1 + \\dots + x_n = p\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "9e6f091d-8e94-4790-a021-9e388268e275",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D{\\'e}terminer $\\Gamma_n^0$, $\\Gamma_n^1$, $\\Gamma_n^2$, $\\Gamma_2^n$.",
        "html": "<p>D<span>é</span>terminer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^0\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^1\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^2\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_2^n\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6ee9428e-014e-4df3-acf8-b4e9cc08f70b",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D{\\'e}montrer que $\\Gamma_{n+1}^{p+1} = \\Gamma_{n+1}^p + \\Gamma_n^{p+1}$\n    (on classera les $(n+1)$-uplets tels que $x_1 + \\dots + x_{n+1} = p + 1$\n    suivant que $x_1 = 0$ ou non).",
        "html": "<p>D<span>é</span>montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_{n+1}^{p+1} = \\Gamma_{n+1}^p + \\Gamma_n^{p+1}\\)</span> (on classera les <span class=\"math inline\">\\((n+1)\\)</span>-uplets tels que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x_1 + \\dots + x_{n+1} = p + 1\\)</span> suivant que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x_1 = 0\\)</span> ou non).</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3e7d0503-a90b-4d18-8824-6cac5d04c80b",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "En d{\\'e}duire que $\\Gamma_n^p = C_{n+p-1}^p$.",
        "html": "<p>En d<span>é</span>duire que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^p = C_{n+p-1}^p\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d561c3bb-e910-4aa0-b624-4746ff69c68a",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$\\Gamma_n^0 = 1$, $\\Gamma_n^1 = n$, $\\Gamma_n^2 = \\frac {n(n+1)}2$,\n    $\\Gamma_2^n = n+1$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^0 = 1\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^1 = n\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_n^2 = \\frac {n(n+1)}2\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\Gamma_2^n = n+1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
